The paper focuses on accelerating 3D Convolutional Neural Networks (3D CNNs) for video recognition, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV) and augmented reality (cs.AR). The paper also mentions the importance of video traffic, which falls under multimedia (cs.MM). The design of the novel accelerator and software infrastructure involves optimization and parameter tuning, which are topics in machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE).
